description:
Official Solicitation 

The direct route to a man's heart is through his stomach. But when Hasegawa tries winning a guy over by making him lunch, the results are disastrous. No surprise -- her nickname is "The Chef Assassin." Does Belldandy have any hope of teaching her how to prepare the perfect lunchbox in just one day? Especially with Urd secretly whipping up a love whammy to give that meal a special kick?
name: The Lunchbox of Love

description:
Official Solicitation

September's a bit late to go to the ocean, but when Urd tells him that the way to be with Belldandy forever is to pledge his love on Three Sisters Rock under a starry September sky, Keiichi is willing to take the plunge. The only problem: Keiichi can't swim, Skuld is dead set to stop him from snagging her sister, and . . . since when was Urd ever right anyway? Anything can happen when three goddesses go to the seashore.
name: Meet Me By The Seashore

description:
Official Solicitation 

Skuld's been moody. Skuld's been morose. The youngest of the three goddesses just can't get Keiichi Morisato out of her head, no mattter how hard she tries. Determined to prove that she isn't in love with Belldandy's boyfriend, Skuld asks Keiichi out for a date. But everything he does for her just makes those troubling feelings stronger. And everything Urd does to turn the date into a disaster is stopped by, of all people, Belldandy herself!
name: You're So Bad

description: The perfect jumping-on point for any and all readers and it's FREE! When rogue mega-billionaires with world-destroying technology threaten the safety of the entire world and the moon Thor and Iron Man join forces! In time for the exciting launch of new stories and a bold new direction for Invincible Iron Man and Thor, superstars Matt Fraction and John Romita Jr. team up to bring you two of Marvel's heaviest hitters like you've never seen them before!
name: Iron Man/Thor

description:
Official Solicitation 

What's faster than a speeding bullet and leaps tall buildings in a single bound? In Japan, it's a ninja, of course! And now the demon Mara, in her ceaseless campaign against the goddesses, has summoned up Ninja Master Kodama, mistress of confusion, to sow ill will among the sisters. It's easy enough to set Urd and Skuld at each other's throats, but can she use her more "charming" powers to split up Belldandy and Keiichi?
name: Ninja Master #1

description:
Official Solicitation 

Kodama has given up the life of a ninja to follow Belldandy, but the ninja code is merciless and any who leaves a Ninja clan is marked for certain death. And it's Kodama's old friends Hikari and Senrigan who have been sent to kill the runaway and save the ninja clan's honor. Belldandy may be able to persuade Kodama and even Hikari to lay down their swords, but can she turn the hearts of a whole household of battling mini-ninjaettes?
name: Ninja Master #2

description:
Official Solicitation 

It's hard to live under the same roof with the love of your life when you can never get time to be alone. But when Urd and Skuld are called back to Goddess Central for training, Keiichi's excited fantasies of quality time with Belldandy are dashed to pieces. Exhausted by the spell she used to stop the ninja invasion, Belldandy collapses. With no one around to help him, Keiichi must figure out which medicine to use to revive his love. His only choice: try the medicine out on himself first, and see what happens!
name: Miss Keiichi #1

description:
Official Solicitation 

Keiichi has his girlfriend back. Problem is, he's turned part way into a girl himself! Well, why not just undo the magic, Urd? Not so easy when Urd's jealous old boyfriend the Troubadour arrives, singing songs of love and threatening to turn any man living under the same roof into a nest of worms and caterpillars! Can Keiichi be woman enough to fool the Troubadour? And can Urd be woman enough to withstand his songs of "Jealous Love"?
name: Miss Keiichi #2

description:
Official Solicitation 

Tamiya and Otaki have entered the Auto Club in a race, and now they've disappeared. Keiichi gets elected acting club president and must lead the club in the vicious Hill Climb race. Can Keiichi save the club's bacon all by himself? Or will he learn that sometimes friends in need are friends indeed?
name: It's Lonely At The Top

description:
Official Solicitation 

Keiichi gets a love letter! And the soft-hearted dweeb isn't tough enough to turn the girl down, even for Belldandy. So imagine his surprise when the devastatingly cute Shiho Sakakibara turns out to be an amateur exorcist, intent on freeing Keiichi's house of evil spirits. But, did we happen to mention the wordamateur?
name: Fallen Angel

description:
Official Solicitation 

What are big brothers for? When the arrogant young studs of the Nekomi Baseball Club try a squeeze play on Megumi and her tiny Softball Club, it's up to Keiichi to help his little sister keep her club alive, and win a playoff match for the right to use the baseball diamond for practice. Of course, Megumi has three goddesses on her side. But the Baseball Club will stop at nothing to win the game, and get Megumi and the goddesses to work for them as Baseball Club gophers!
name: Play The Game

description: Get an inside peek at Spider-Man’s largest event, as the creators of the Clone Saga deliver this informative, and fun, read!
name: Puppet

description:
Official Solicitation 

Everyone loves a puppy, right? Well, not Keiichi Morisato. When Megumi brings over a darling lost puppy, and Skuld falls head over heels for the little butterball, Keiichi puts his foot down: no dogs allowed! What he can't tell even his beloved Belldandy is that he really loves dogs -- but that his own pup died in an accident that he's never been able to forget. Can anyone, canine or human, find a way into Keiichi's heart?
name: Sorrow, Fear Not

description: This is a preview for the Fame: Lady Gaga issue from Blue Water Comics. It also includes a preview of Fame: Taylor Swift and The Puppy Sister.
name: Free Comic Book Day Preview

volume.name: Fame: Lady Gaga - Free Comic Book Day

description:
Official Solicitation 

When the goddesses win a free trip to a hot springs resort, it turns out they're not the only deities off on vacation. Demon First Class Mara is checked into the same rustic retreat! When the old enemies call a truce, Keiichi gets to see a different side of Urd -- the half-demon who used to be best friends with their arch-nemesis!
name: The Devil In Miss Urd #1

description:
Official Solicitation

The evil demon Mara is once again up to no good. She's building a clone from a lock of Urd's hair that she swiped from Urd at the hot-springs resort. The purpose of the clone: Mara wants to merge the 100 proof demon blood of Urd and the 100 proof demon blood of her clone to make a pure 200 Proof Demonic Urd!
name: The Devil In Miss Urd #2

description:
Official Solicitation 

Mara has brought out the devil in Miss Urd, all right, and this new demon Urd is ready to rock `n' roll. The only ones who may be able to stop her -- Skuld and Angel Urd -- are locked up tight in Mara's secret hideout. But stop her they must because she's on her way to seduce Keiichi and send a brokenhearted Belldandy back to heaven!
name: The Devil In Miss Urd #3

description:
Official Solicitation 

Skuld has saved Belldandy from Urd's demonic twin clone, but the battle has just begun. How can you tell the real Urd from the evil clone, especially when both of them start acting like goody two-shoes? Will Skuld be able to figure out who the bad one is before it runs out of control and destroys the world?
name: The Devil In Miss Urd #4

description:
Official Solicitation 

Two Urds, one body! When Urd's demonic doppleganger realizes her cloned body is beginning to fall apart, she sets her sights on driving the real Urd out of her original body. The only way to stop her may be for Urd the angel to destroy Urd the devil, and save the whole world from destruction! After all, the light cannot exist without the dark. Right, Skuld?!
name: The Devil In Miss Urd #5

description:
Official Solicitation 

Now that the battle with Urd's evil doppleganger is over, Keiichi and the goddesses are stuck with the problem of what to do with the extra copy of Urd's skin they used in the battle. It's not the sort of thing anybody, or any goddess, would want to have around. But what if someone isn't a goddess, and isn't really a "body" either? Good deeds break out all over town when Banpei the robot discovers a new identiy, as SuperUrd, defender of justice!
name: SuperUrd

description:
Official Solicitation

Third time's a charm. Or is it the fourth time? Keiichi just wants to make a phone call. But when his dial-tone karma connects him to heaven yet again, suddenly he has a fourth goddess on his hands. And to make it worse, this fourth goddess Peorth and Belldandy may be old friends, but now they work for rival goddess agencies! And Peorth is sure that she can give Keiichi what he wants better than Belldandy herself! Can you spell a three-letter word that ends with... X?
name: The Fourth Goddess #1

description:
Official Solicitation 

Most guys would be glad to have a bodacious babe promise to grant his every desire. But not Keiichi Morisato. At least, not when the little sex bomb from heaven is Peorth, and her competitive wiles are threatening to drive him away from his beloved Belldandy. He's doing his best. But how long can Keiichi resist this kind of full-court pressure?
name: The Fourth Goddess #2

description:
Official Solicitation 

Service with a snarl! When Peorth gets under Urd and Skuld's skin, Belldandy's sisters decide to prove who's the most helpful goddess of all. And Keiichi has to judge the competition, like it or not. The customer may be king, but not when the help are all goddesses, with egos as powerful as their spells. Can Belldandy repair the damage, and keep Peorth away from her man, all at the same time?
name: The Fourth Goddess #3

description:
Official Solicitation  

When Peorth tampers with Urd's collection of love potions, the battle for Keiichi can only go from bad to worse. Anyone he looks at falls instantly in love, including his own sister! Can Keiichi fend off Megumi, Urd, and Skuld as well as his nemesis Peorth? And more to the point, should he or should he not look at Belldandy?
name: The Fourth Goddess #4

description:
Official Solicitation 

Peorth, falling steadily deeper into infatuation with Keiichi, decides to try the old-fashioned approach. She arranges for the perfect date, hoping it will lead to "granting his heart's desire." But her plans go awry when the goddesses decide to tag along.
name: The Fourth Goddess #5

description:
Official Solicitation 

Tamiya, Keiichi's old boss at the Motor Club, may be as dense as a rock, but he doesn't have a heart of stone. One look at Peorth, and the big lug is hopelessly in love. Hopelessly, because Peorth sees Tamiya's affections as a new tool to use in her ongoing battle for Keiichi's heart and mind. The more Peorth pumps up Tamiya's ego, the farther he has to fall. Can Keiichi save his friend from a broken heart?
name: The Fourth Goddess #6

description:
Official Solicitation 

For the life of her, Belldandy can't remember what she did to get Peorth so mad at her years ago, but no matter, what are sisters for, anyway? Urd and Skuld pursue Peorth with a syringe full of truth serum. And everyone gets more truth than they bargained for!
name: The Fourth Goddess #7

description:
Official Solicitation  

Peorth cannot leave Keiichi and Belldandy alone! She hounds the poor lovers for what she sees as the goddess' failure to satisfy Keiichi's suppressed hunger for sex. Peorth is so obsessed with the "S" word; she's obviously forgotten about the "L" word.
name: The Fourth Goddess #8

description: Every single moment of the last year has led to this fight between Red Robin and Ra's al Ghul. Who has Ra's been talking to all this time in the shadows? Why was Lucius Fox so desperate to find Tim Drake? And why was Tim so certain that Bruce Wayne is alive in issue #1? All questions are answered.
name: Collision, Part 4

description:
Official Solicitation

In order to teach Skuld to be more self-reliant, Belldandy refuses to use her goddess powers to help Skuld learn to ride a bicycle. But will Belldandy's lesson in learning to rely on one's own inner strength be for naught when Skuld meets... a boy?!
name: Childhood's End #1

description:
Official Solicitation  

Skuld is beginning to develop her powers at last, following the bicycle breakthrough. Her progress is furthered by her feelings for Sentaro the bicycle boy. After all, without thinking of others more than she thinks of herself, Skuld cannot emerge as a mature goddess.
name: Childhood's End #2

description:
Official Solicitation 

For chance, Sayoko sees Belldandy emerge from a mirror. But she still refuses to believe Belldandy is a goddess, and becomes so suspicious that she attracts an "Anki," a creature that lives on people's trusting heart energy. Belldandy must convince Sayoko that goddesses are real before Sayoko turns into a paranoid psychotic!
name: The Queen And The Goddess

description:
Official Solicitation  

A woman suddenly appears at the Auto Club who is dauntingly good at all things automotive. It turns out she is the legendary first manager of the club, and before Keiichi knows it, he's been challenged to a race--a race he thinks will determine whether he's qualified to succeed Tamiya as head of the club himself!
name: Hail To The Chief #1

description:
Official Solicitation 

When Fujimi orders a cleanup of the Auto Club premises, the members discover a map to the Auto Club "treasure." Keiichi, Belldandy, and Hasegawa finally discover the treasure, but a pot o' gold, it ain't -- it's more like a can of worms!
name: Hail To The Chief #2

description:
Official Solicitation 

Keiichi's about to graduate, which means...it's time to find a job! The only problem is, he's waited so long to get started that there aren't any jobs left at the school recruitment office. But when an old friend calls from Wyvern, a manufacturer of custom parts for motorcycles, Keiichi gets job interview with the CEO himself. Can Urd's magical business-suit inventory and Skuld's job interview machine get him ready for the big day?
name: Hail To The Chief #3

name: Bloom County

description: Eisner-nominated ATOMIC ROBO knows that the rain forests of South America hid many secrets, but not as deadly as The Terror Bird! Forgotten by time, these prehistoric apex predators are primed to devastate the modern world! The word 'terror' is right there in its name. Plus, previews of 2010 adventures of Red 5 favorites and new faces, including the first chapter of Box 13, comiXology's hit iPhone and Web comic!
name: Flight of the Terror Birds / Feeding Time / Box 13 Chapter 1

volume.name: Atomic Robo / Neozoic / Box 13 Free Comic Book Day 2010

description:
Kid (and historical figures, of course) helps an unlucky couple. And how!

Her highness and Silk in their own story!
A machine of Father time is broken, and it causes Julius Caesar and some of his soldiers to appear in present day, and cause problems in the states!

Synopsis

Doctor Solar, Man of the Atom & Magnus, Robot Fighter The dawn of a new age of superhero excitement begins on Free Comic Book Day (FCBD) as Dark Horse Comics proudly presents the return of two of the most legendary characters in the annals of comics, Doctor Solar, Man of the Atom and Magnus, Robot Fighter, re-imagined for the 21st century by another comics legend, writer Jim Shooter! This FCBD extravaganza offers all-new Solar and Magnus stories, each heralding new series launches in Summer of 2010, and features interior art by fan-favorite Dennis Calero (X-Men Noir) and cover art by Raymond Swanland.   
 

Inside the Issue

Inside this Issue Doctor Solar has just got his powers and set out to stop his first criminal.  In the Mangus Story Magnus fights a couple of sentient robots.  Leeja is also introduced here.  Both stories are single shot stories that set up the new series.
name: Fallout / Eyes to the Blind

volume.name: Free Comic Book Day: Doctor Solar, Man of the Atom / Magnus, Robot Fighter

description: Did you miss out on the book Comic Book Resources called one of the surprise hits of 2009? Don't be left in The Dark this year as Th3rd World Studios presents not only a recap of the toys' first adventure from Volume I, The Dark, but also a first look at Volume 2, The Jungle set to launch in June. Also, get an exclusive look at the first chapter of Th3rd World's adaptation of the New York Times Bestselling novel, The Mortal Instruments, City of Bones, by Cassandra Clare. This young adult fantasy series centers on the life of fifteen-year-old Clary Fray and her discovery of a bizarre unseen world filled with Shadowhunters, a secret tribe of warriors dedicated to ridding the earth of demons.
name: Volume 1: The Dark Recap / Part One: Dark Descent

volume.name: The Stuff of Legend / The Mortal Instruments

name: Too Tough To Handle
The Roots Of Evil
Cottonwool Commandos

description: One of the Winged Warrior's deadliest foes returns in a one-shot devoted to the newest incarnation of Hawkman! A foe nearly as ancient as Hawkman makes his presence known (in a story written by Geoff Johns with art by Patrick Gleason & Christian Alamy). Plus, the DEO investigates the mysterious Nth metal (written by Dan Curtis Johnson & J.H. Williams III with art by Greg Scott & Mick Gray). Rounding out the issue are profile pages focusing on the Hawks, their villains and the supporting cast of the hit new series, by an array of artists including HAWKMAN's Rags Morales & Michael Bair, Walter Simonson, and more!

This is what you REALLY want! Larry Hama continues his original and ground-breaking G.I. JOE: A REAL AMERICAN HERO saga with the VERY NEXT ISSUE (but, you know, 15 years later). G.I. JOE has closed its doors, leaving COBRA to pillage, burn, and plunder!
name: FCBD

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: In this stylized book of mystery and science fiction, a drug-dealing car thief must discover the secret behind his visions in order to save the world. Twenty years after the devastating Cataclysm, society has been separated into sectors in which the rich are able to enjoy machine-generated weather and sunlight while the poor are forced to live an eternally dank and dark existence. Banished to the dismal Sector 5, the angst-ridden Beezer discovers that the corrupt city police are hunting him because of his experiential visions of a pre-apocalyptic world. Now Earth's reluctant savior must learn his true origin and the meaning of his visions before he is captured and killed.
name: TPB

description:
The Tick "releases" himself from a padded cell and a strait jacket to fight crime in the city. Unfortunately for Tick and The City he is unable to recognize the crime around him. Luckily he can stop it anyway. Some of the confusion happens with the Tick's surveillance view finder camera.

Afterwords the Tick goes to a diner that looks exactly like he 1942 Nighthawks painting by Edward Hopper. He has some funny conversations with the characters in the painting and ends up hyperventilating himself and passing out as he breaths in and out through a straw.

He wakes up in a subway and thinks he is in the belly of a whale. Caped Wonder tries to save him and hilarity ensues. A relationship for the two is set up for the future.
name: FCBD 2010

volume.name: Tick's Free Comic Book Day Special Edition

name: Solo Smith
